<font size="3" color="#363636"><b>Lotus of the Rings!</b></font><br>
<font size="2">Posted on Saturday, January 19 @ 05:54:08 EST by <br><br><a href="search.php?query=&amp;topic=1"><img src="images/topicseverquest.gif" border="0" Alt="Everquest" align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10"></a>
<font size="2" color="#505050">The night of the rings!  Both of our guild events this evening were ring themed: 10th Ring War and Ring of Fire.  The evening began in The Great Divide were we came to the aid of the Dain and his stumpy people.  Please, for a moment pretend we didn&#8217;t just slay the Dain!  In fact, many of our guild being maligned by the Dwarven folk  makes this event rather entertaining.  We continually have to avoid the Dwarven troops around the landscape set to help out.  This particular ring war may have been the smoothest to date.  There were only three deaths that I counted during the entirety of the war.  When a scout went linkdead, 3 others jumped in quickly to take over.  When a tank fell, another was right there.  Execution was virtuously harmonious.   <br><br>

<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/herdofdorfs.jpg"><br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/axemen.jpg"><br><br>

After a quick a decisive expungement of Narandi, the war was over and Dwarven freedom maintained!  Awards were as follows: <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2171">Quixotim</a></b> (ring recipient), <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2185">Dalebra</a></b> (<b><a href="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/crownofnarandi.jpg">Crown of Narandi</a></b>), Drakkun (earring &#8211; no pic!), Purite (Eye of Narandi &#8211; no pic!), Darkweb (neck), <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37204">Ishan</a></b> (mask), and Bahsh (Narandi&#8217;s Lance &#8211; no pic!).  On a personal note, I&#8217;d like sincerely thank everyone that came to help &#8211; your support was awesome.

<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/ringofdainfrostreaveriv.jpg">
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/chokerofthewretched.jpg">
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/faceguardofbentosthehero.jpg"><br><br>

Next on the evening&#8217;s agenda was the Ring of Fire event in AC.  After several rounds of simple fights, this event quickly goes from benign to malignant.  We were stymied by the enormity of pops during the 5th wave commander, given that we had on two enchanters and no bards.  Nevertheless, even with the Underlord (6th wave commander) spawning during the 5th wave commander&#8217;s fight, we bested him before the remainder of our troops were defeated by the Underlord.  <br><br>

<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/rofgroup.jpg">
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/rofcorpses011802.jpg"><br><br>

Notable rewards for the evening went to Wynnter (a bracelet for which I failed to get any information on), Brooh (<b><a href="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/earringoffondmemories.jpg">Earring of Fond Memories</a></b>), and <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1599">Gimick</a></b> (<b><a href="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/warmastersribcage.jpg">Warmaster&#8217;s Ribcage</a></b>)<br><br>


<b>Comments from The Cult: </b><br>
Ebobulous has Master Plan: <br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/ebobandson.jpg"><br><br>

Wyen gives me advice before the ring war: <br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/wyenadvice.jpg"><br><br>

Skrabbit makes the &#8220;best use&#8221; of clerics when ring war waves get harder: <br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/clericsmustnuke.jpg"><br><br>

Quizer feels guilty over being late! <br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/quizerwantstodie.jpg"><br><br>

CH a dragon once (or five times) and forever pay the price: <br>
<img src="http://www.webcmg.com/lcpics/danerahealerofmobs.jpg"><br><br>

<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2171">Quixotim Omniscience</a></b><br>
Erudite Crusader<BR>
<a href="http://www.lotuscult.com">Lotus Cult</a><br>
E-mail: quixotm@webcmg.com 
<br></font>
